cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper deals with representing meaning in the form of high dimensional vectors, which is a common technique in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses sparse vector decomposition, which is a technique used in machine learning and data analysis, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also explores ways in which the tool can be used for vector-based reasoning, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of semantic vectors in computer vision (cs.CV) and biologically inspired architectures (cs.NE), making these categories also likely.
